{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/capsule\/geometrygroup()"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Capsule"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Capsule\/geometryGroup()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed down to each subview."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"ItemView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" may be added and removed at different times the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applied."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from its parent view.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE13geometryGroupQryF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore7CapsuleV","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"geometryGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"}],"role":"symbol","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Render\/RendererEffect\/RendererEffect.swift#L304","fileName":"RendererEffect.swift"},"roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","platforms":[{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"13.0","beta":false},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"10.15","beta":false},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"13.0","beta":false},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0","beta":false},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"6.0","beta":false}],"title":"geometryGroup()","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore"},"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View":{"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/view","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that represents part of your appâ€™s user interface and provides"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifiers that you use to configure views."}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","title":"View","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Capsule/geometryGroup()":{"kind":"symbol","title":"geometryGroup()","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Capsule\/geometryGroup()","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/capsule\/geometrygroup()","abstract":[{"text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from its parent view.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"